Feathers

Amantecas - produce feathered goods
Warrior costumes and shields made from feathers

Feathered objects were destined for elite and state use

Featherworking production was expensive and complicated

Tribute in feathers was not the same as tribute in feathered objects


Ceramics

Black-on-Orange

Not an item of tribute

Tenochtitlan had a lot of producers of ceramics

Many towns made ceramic goods, was not centralized to Tenochtitlan


Obsidian

Volcanic glass

Believed it was important because of its qualities (shiny and green)

green - Pachuca
gray - Otumba
